tip.text: The coffee is robust and nutty! Cheerful and friendly service in this cafe which doubles up as a place for art classes. Quiet and nice in weekend afternoons - perfect for a cuppa & some reading.
Lovely breads made from the heart. Chef Francis even made his own blueberry jam & butter. Definitely coming back to this quaint bakery.
The portions are huge and must be shared or it can get quite "jelak". Beef ribs are soft, and pulled apart easily. Skip the calamari starters unless you like your batter thick and hard.
A hidden cafe. Nice all-day breakfast menu with good portions. Don't miss the fluffy, light waffles.

tip.text: Love the lemon strawberry pie - zesty with a tinge of sweetness. Great service, lovely pies, good friends and charming decor all make for a wonderful lazy afternoon.
Service not that great. Staff seems to be more concerned about expat customers' babies that I felt that having to order was actually bothering them. So-so coffee.
Vanilla souffle is definitely worth the wait! Crack open the crispy crust to reveal an egg tart like interior.
Bacon, ham and onion quiche - slightly sweet pastry crust balances well with savory filling. This, coming from a non-quiche person. Love the seasonal Orange Cappuccino during the CNY hols.

venue.name: Chye Seng Huat Hardware Coffee Bar

tip.text: Love the coffee here. Robust, roasty. I don't think I can go a week without craving for a cuppa.
Chocolate Sea Salt Caramel Tart is simply gorgeous. That's coming from someone who doesn't like caramel. Lemon Drizzle will have you going back for more! Tea is so-so. Coffee not bad. Nice concept!
Oh-my crepe cake sandwiched with strawberries. For that quality, tea is super overpriced.

tip.text: Great disappointment. Over-rated, over-priced. Waited 50mins, and something that was $25 tasted like $6.50. Juz look at this egg benedict. Tea like cough syrup.
Nice place for a lazy weekend. Coffee is better than Forty Hands, though a little on the thin side. I would have prefer a creamier, more robust blend. Love the long top.
Coffee is sour. Think the beans are burnt. Didn't like the sandwich here.
The quality of creme brulee and tart that I ordered here was different from the ones I had in Paris and Shanghai. A little disappointed. What's more? The service could really be better.
The fruit tea is superb - refreshing and soothing to the soul~! I love the pear tea and the lychee tea. Go without sugar and have a go at the fruits in the teapot. Skip the cheesecake tho!
My choices: Ekeme, chocolate eclair.
Food for social cause! Love the decor here. Better to come here before 5.30pm for the all-day breakfast.

Love the beer here! It's a good place to chill with friends after a hard day's work & to avoid crowd. Salad is beautifully done with just a zest of lemon juice. Love the chicken schnitzel.
Nice concept & merchandise. Choice of drink too little - but they have sarsi, so I forgive them. Area to sit & rest ur feet. Tempting to buy one of those vintage-style toys and cute little notebooks.

With such a humongous list of teas, it can be a mind-boggling affair to choose. Go with your favorite kind (darjeeling/earl grey/green/white) & experiment! Macaroons r too sweet. Fav tea: Amour de The
